args: In the years after the attack on the caravan,\nI continued to work as a mercenary.
The vaunted warrior does not disappoint!\nShe broke through their lines by herself!
Ain't no way we could ever pull that off!
Who told you two it was break time?\nWe've got a fort to capture, so MOVE!

Back then, I never faltered in battle—why would I,
knowing I could not die? As a result, I led the way
to victory in multiple conflicts, and soon found
myself with ever more mercenary acquaintances.
Looks like everyone has a glass,\nso let us toast to victory!
You're the reason this job was so easy,\nKhan, so good on ya! Bwa ha ha ha!
Oh, I saw plenty of mighty blows struck\nby the rest of you. But in any case,\nI hope we fight again together soon.
Khan's somethin' else... Strong, gutsy,\nbeautiful... Think she's got a boyfriend?
Er, this is your first time working\nwith Khan, isn't it?
Here's a tip: Quit while you're ahead.
Hello, Marie. You want something to eat?\nAnything you like, my treat.

Out of obligation, yeah. Couple years back,
a caravan she was guarding got waylaid,
and that kid was the only other survivor.
Afterward, she adopted her as her own.

A whole line'a suitors have tried their luck,
but they all meet the same end as her
enemies in battle. Seems that little cutie
is the only love she needs in life.
Where'd you go this time, Mama?
Heh. You do love my stories.
Yeah! They're super fun,\nand you're SO cool in them!
Let's see, then. Where should I begin?
I'm sorry, but could you head home first,\nMarie? I need to get some air, but I\npromise I'll be along in short order.
...You've been watching me since we were\nat the restaurant, so you might as well\ncome out and save us both the hassle.
A pleasure to meet you, Lady Yoshitsune.\nI am an envoy of Lord Yoritomo.
No, my lady. I come only to inform you\nthat Lord Yoritomo deeply regrets your past\ntreatment and wishes to make amends.
Lies. My brother would never say such.
But it's true I feel no threat from you.\nSo if you're not here for my head,\nwhat's REALLY going on?

Are you aware that Lord Yoritomo has
become leader of the Rooster Wyrmclan,
one of the twelve branch clans that hold
claim to the leadership of the shogunate?
Yes. Our family is distantly related to\nthe shogunal family, which is why we were\nselected to be one of its branch houses.

Each of these Wyrmclans has a leader
who forms a pact with a dragon—but in
doing so, their soul is diminished,
along with their lifespan.

Lord Yoritomo has precious little time left.
However, his heir, Lord Yoriie, is still quite
young, and my lord worries governing will
prove a challenging prospect for him.

Ah, now I see. He wants me to serve as an
intermediary in the line of succession until
my nephew is of age. How very selfish—
and how so very like him.

Your lord brother is well aware of that.
However, if you can bring together the
Rooster Wyrmclan, would that not grant
your fallen vassals peace?
What would you know about them?

A vassal wishes to see their master grow
in distinction. And though the position may
be temporary, you could become a shogun
candidate—or even the shogun herself.

No matter how you distinguish yourself as
a mercenary, you will always be a grunt.
Were I one of your vassals, I would feel a
death on your behalf to be meaningless.
Take what time you need to think this over.\nThink about why you were kept alive.
Morning, Mama! It's lovely weather today.
Good morning, Marie. I'm going to the\nblacksmith today, so be a good girl and\nwatch over things here while I'm gone.
(＂Why I was kept alive＂...\nWhat way of living, I wonder, would best\nserve as an offering to my fallen vassals...)
There you are! Er, I mean... Hey, Khan.\nFunny runnin' into you here.
Hello. Did you all come to have some\nweapon maintenance done as well?
Just consulting on some equipment.\nHe wanted to pick something good.
Oh, er, yeah. Would you mind helping\nme pick out some quality gear, Khan?
Sorry, but when the work is done\non my blade, I have to head home.
C'mon, just help us a little!
I can't believe I let those fools drag me\ninto this and delay me for so long.\nI'll have to apologize to Marie...
Marie? Daniela? What's going on with\nthese decorations and all that food?
Ha! We did it! Operation Slow-Her-Down\nwas a rousing success!
You really do think of nothing but battle...\nIt's your BIRTHDAY! Remember?
Marie told us her plan during the banquet.
She wanted us to help throw a party.
And seeing how much we owe you for\ntaking care of us on the battlefield,\nnot a soul hesitated to jump in.
I don't know what to say...
I just wanted you to be happy, Mama.\n...So how did I do?
You did amazing, child. I'm delighted.
Yes. I'm staying in North Grastaea.
And giving up on the path of success?\nWhat would your vassals think?
Do you know what the last thing Benkei\never said to me was?
He said that he wanted me to be happy,\nThat's the reason I was kept alive.

And what makes me happy are my family
and comrades here in North Grastaea.
Now please go, and give my regards to
my brother and nephew.
For a while after that, I had a warm, good\nlife filled with the happiness I sought.

But in all that happiness, my mind never
caught on to the heartbreak that awaits
an undying woman. ...You know what I
mean, Marie?
